castVote(uint256,uint256).details: Cast a vote using fractions of an NFT

params.tokenId: The ID of the NFT This function marks fractions as voted and prevents further delegation

claimRoyalties(uint256).details: Claim royalties for fractions of an NFT

constructor.details: Constructor initializes the ERC721 with name and symbol

params.name: The name of the NFT collection
params.symbol: The symbol of the NFT collection

delegateFractions(uint256,address,uint25.details: Delegate fractions to another address for voting (can only delegate once)

params.amount: The number of fractions to delegate

distributeRoyalties(uint256).details: Distribute royalties for an NFT to fraction owners proportionally

getFraction(uint256,address).details: Get fraction details for an address and token

returns.owner: Address owning these fractions, amount Number of fractions owned,          isDelegate Whether or not these are delegated fractions,                      delegatedTo Who they're delegated too if so (address 0 otherwise),                          hasVoted If this member voted with these fractions already and lastVoteTimestamp The timestamp when it was voted

getVotingPower(address).details: Get voting power of an address

returns._0: The voting power of the address

hasVotedOnProposal(address,uint256).details: Check if an address has voted on a proposal

returns._0: Whether the address has voted on the proposal

mint(address,uint256,string,string,strin.details: Mint a new NFT with fractional capabilities

params.eligibleForRageQuit: Whether this NFT's fractions are eligible for rage quit
params.name: The name of the NFT
params.to: The address that will receive the NFT
params.totalFractions: Total number of fractions for this NFT
params.uri: The URI of the NFT metadata

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

rageQuit().details: Execute rage quit, burning all owned fractions for eligible members Implemented with a YUL assembly block for bonus point

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

tokenURI(uint256).details: Overridden tokenURI function to return custom metadata URI

transferFractions(uint256,address,uint25.details: Transfer fractions of an NFT from one address to another

params.amount: The number of fractions to transfer

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
